entities.description: bookrag is a model or architecture evaluated for efficiency in terms of query time and token consumption
graph based rag methods are existing approaches to which bookrag is compared in terms of time and token costs
text based rag approaches are methods that generally have lower latency and token usage due to not processing images
multi modal methods are a category of approaches among which bookrag maintains balanced efficiency
docetl is the strongest baseline to which bookrag is compared  with bookrag reducing token consumption by an order of magnitude
figure 5 is an image that illustrates the evaluation of efficiency in terms of query time and token consumption

relations.description: bookrag is compared to existing graph based rag methods  maintaining comparable time and token costs
bookrag is contrasted with text based rag approaches  which generally have lower latency and token usage
bookrag maintains a balanced efficiency among multi modal methods
bookrag reduces token consumption by an order of magnitude compared to the strongest baseline  docetl
figure 5 illustrates the evaluation of bookrag s efficiency in terms of query time and token consumption
